# Clerk Auth Rules

## Setup
- middleware.ts MUST use `clerkMiddleware()` from `@clerk/nextjs/server`
- ALWAYS define public routes in `createRouteMatcher()`
- Protected routes automatically redirect to Clerk's sign-in

## Server-Side Auth
- Server components: `import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs/server'`
- ALWAYS destructure `userId` first, check for null immediately
- For full user object: use `currentUser()` — only when needed (slower)
- NEVER use `getAuth()` in App Router — use `auth()` instead

## Client-Side Auth
- USE `useAuth()` for auth state in client components
- USE `useUser()` for user data in client components
- USE `` for pre-built profile button
- USE `` and `` for auth triggers

## Webhooks
- ALWAYS verify webhook signature with `svix` package
- Webhook handler: `app/api/webhooks/clerk/route.ts`
- Handle events: `user.created`, `user.updated`, `user.deleted`
- SYNC user data to Supabase `profiles` table on `user.created`

## Example — Correct Middleware
```typescript
// middleware.ts
import { clerkMiddleware, createRouteMatcher } from '@clerk/nextjs/server'

const isPublicRoute = createRouteMatcher([
  '/',
  '/sign-in(.*)',
  '/sign-up(.*)',
  '/api/webhooks(.*)',
  '/pricing',
])

export default clerkMiddleware(async (auth, req) => {
  if (!isPublicRoute(req)) {
    await auth.protect()
  }
})

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/((?!_next|[^?]*\\.(?:html?|css|js(?!on)|jpe?g|webp|png|gif|svg|ttf|woff2?|ico|csv|docx?|xlsx?|zip|webmanifest)).*)', '/(api|trpc)(.*)'],
}
```

## Example — Protected Server Component
```typescript
import { auth, currentUser } from '@clerk/nextjs/server'
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation'

export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth()
  if (!userId) redirect('/sign-in')

  // Only fetch full user when you need profile data
  const user = await currentUser()

  return 
}
```
